sky.tennis.uk.title: ATP/WTA Tour Classic Matches

sky.tennis.uk.title: Connors v Borg 1976

sky.tennis.uk.title: Laver v Roche 1969
sky.tennis.uk.description: In the men's singles final at the 1969 US Open, history was made, as Rod Laver became the only man in the Open Era to win the Calendar Grand Slam - owning all four majors in the same year.

sky.tennis.uk.title: ATP Final: Doha

sky.tennis.uk.title: ATP Final: Rio
sky.tennis.uk.description: In the final of the Rio Open, defending champion Sebastian Baez takes on Alexander Muller. The Frenchman enters his second ATP final of the year after victory in Hong Kong. (23.02)

sky.tennis.uk.title: US Open 2013: Nadal v Djokovic
sky.tennis.uk.description: Revisit the 2013 US Open final as Rafael Nadal overpowered Novak Djokovic to win a second Flushing Meadows title.

sky.tennis.uk.title: US Open 2019: Nadal v Medvedev
sky.tennis.uk.description: Rafael Nadal won his 19th Grand Slam and fourth US Open title with victory over Daniil Medvedev in 2019 at Flushing Meadows.

sky.tennis.uk.title: WTA Final: Abu Dhabi
sky.tennis.uk.description: 2021 Olympic gold medallist Belinda Bencic looks to capture her first title since returning from maternity leave, as the Swiss star faces Ashlyn Krueger in the Abu Dhabi final. (08.02)

sky.tennis.uk.title: WTA Final: Transylvania

sky.tennis.uk.title: ATP Final: Montpellier

sky.f1.uk.description: It's lights out for the United States Grand Prix. A growing threat in the title fight, Max Verstappen has pole from Lando Norris as championship leader Oscar Piastri starts in P6. (19.10)

sky.f1.uk.title: Monaco F1 GP Highlights

sky.f1.uk.title: Spanish F1 GP Highlights

sky.f1.uk.title: Canadian F1 GP Highlights

sky.f1.uk.title: Dutch F1 GP Highlights

sky.f1.uk.title: Spanish F1 GP Highlights
sky.f1.uk.description: It's an all-papaya front row as McLaren lead the way with Oscar Piastri from Lando Norris. Max Verstappen and George Russell form the second row, while Lewis Hamilton starts P5. (01.06)

sky.f1.uk.title: Canadian F1 GP Highlights
sky.f1.uk.description: It's lights out for the Canadian Grand Prix as George Russell and Max Verstappen line-up alongside each other at the front with Oscar Piastri in third. Lando Norris comes from P7. (15.06)

sky.f1.uk.title: Austrian F1 GP Highlights
sky.f1.uk.description: Lando Norris bounces back to take pole alongside Charles Leclerc. Oscar Piastri and Lewis Hamilton share row two, while Max Verstappen starts down in P7 for Red Bull's home race. (29.06)

sky.f1.uk.title: British F1 GP Highlights
sky.f1.uk.description: It's lights out at Silverstone. Max Verstappen shares the front row with Oscar Piastri, while Brits Lando Norris, George Russell and Lewis Hamilton round out the top five. (06.07)

sky.f1.uk.title: Belgian F1 GP Highlights
sky.f1.uk.description: It's lights out at Spa. With eyes on the weather, Lando Norris and Oscar Piastri lock out the front, while Charles Leclerc starts P3. Lewis Hamilton bids to fight through the field. (27.07)

sky.f1.uk.title: Hungarian F1 GP Highlights
sky.f1.uk.description: It's lights out at the Hungaroring. As Charles Leclerc goes up against the McLarens from pole, both Max Verstappen and Lewis Hamilton face tough recovery drives from further back. (03.08)

sky.f1.uk.title: Dutch F1 GP Highlights
sky.f1.uk.description: It's lights out in Zandvoort. Pipping his team mate to pole, Oscar Piastri leads Lando Norris as Max Verstappen looks to spring a surprise from P3 with Isack Hadjar for company. (31.08)

sky.f1.uk.title: Italian F1 GP Highlights
sky.f1.uk.description: It's lights out at Monza. Max Verstappen holds pole from title contenders Lando Norris and Oscar Piastri as Charles Leclerc leads the Ferrari charge with Lewis Hamilton down in P10. (07.09)

sky.f1.uk.title: Azerbaijan F1 GP Highlights
sky.f1.uk.description: In Baku, Max Verstappen leads a mixed-up starting grid with Carlos Sainz and Liam Lawson in podium contention. Lando Norris and Oscar Piastri bid to come through the field. (21.09)

sky.f1.uk.title: Singapore F1 GP Highlights
sky.f1.uk.description: It's lights out at Marina Bay Circuit for the 2025 Singapore Grand Prix. George Russell claims Mercedes' second pole of the season, with Max Verstappen starting in second. (05.10)

sky.f1.uk.title: US F1 GP Highlights
sky.f1.uk.description: It's lights out for the United States Grand Prix. A growing threat in the title fight, Max Verstappen has pole from Lando Norris as championship leader Oscar Piastri starts in P6. (19.10)

sky.f1.uk.title: Mexico City F1 GP Highlights
sky.f1.uk.description: It's lights out in Mexico City. Lando Norris aims to capitalise on a big opening in the title race as the Ferraris of Charles Leclerc and Lewis Hamilton round out the top three. (26.10)

sky.f1.uk.title: Sao Paulo F1 GP Highlights
sky.f1.uk.description: It's lights out at Interlagos. An opportunity presents itself to poleman Lando Norris in the title chase with Oscar Piastri starting P4 and Max Verstappen way down the grid. (09.11)

sky.f1.uk.title: Las Vegas F1 GP Highlights
sky.f1.uk.description: As the lights go out on the Strip for the Las Vegas Grand Prix, championship leader Lando Norris starts from P1 with Max Verstappen behind. Oscar Piastri lines up in fifth place. (23.11)

sky.f1.uk.title: Qatar F1 GP Highlights
sky.f1.uk.description: It's lights out in Qatar. As Lando Norris lines up in P2 a win away from the world championship, it's down to polesitter Oscar Piastri and Max Verstappen to deny the Brit the title. (30.11)

UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Einstein: James May reveals what we need to know about Albert Einstein, his theories, and just what happened to the famous physicist's brain. S2 Ep1

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: James May's Things You Need To Know About Science
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Brains: James cranks open our craniums to find out about behaviour, memory, and much, much more from over 100 billion whizzing neurons. S2 Ep2

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Border Force America's Gatekeepers
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: A refugee from Venezuela tells officers how she paid human traffickers to smuggle her to the Mexico-US border. In Laredo, an American couple are caught smuggling methamphetamine. S2 Ep7

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Border Force America's Gatekeepers
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: A family from Venezuela plead with officers to enter America. In Progreso, a suspected drug dealer is caught smuggling pills in his underpants. S2 Ep8

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: How Britain Worked
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Engineering enthusiast Guy Martin renovates a sawmill in Wensleydale in North Yorkshire and then uses it to make a replica of the first pedal-powered bicycle. S1 Ep2

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Rick Stein's Road to Mexico
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Oaxaca to Chinantlan Mountains: Rick explores the hidden land of Mexico's culinary capital Oaxaca, where you can smell the tropical fruit and Mexico's national cheese of queso oaxacana. S1 Ep6

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Excalibur/Austin 7: A 1970 Excalibur Roadstar, once owned by Roy Orbison, arrives at Thornton le Dale and Derek heads to County Durham to collect a 1935 Austin 7 Ulster that's been rebuilt. S4 Ep1

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Austin A30/BMW Isetta: Two British classics head into to the Mathewsons' auction room, Dave heads to North Manchester to pick up an Austin A30 and a Morris 8 E with an alternative paint job. S4 Ep2

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Extreme Fishing with Robson Green
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Costa Rica: The actor joins some of the world's most skilled fishermen on angling expeditions - here he begins his journey in Costa Rica as he tries to land sailfish. S1 Ep1

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Top Gear
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Petrol-fuelled fun. Jeremy hops in a Mercedes McLaren SLR and races Richard and James, who travel by boat, to Oslo. It's question time for David Dimbleby, who stops by for a chat. S6 Ep6

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Top Gear
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Clarkson has the not-so-latest motoring news with pals Richard Hammond and James May. Good news for white van men as the Ford Transit celebrates its birthday. S6 Ep7

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Hairy Bikers' Best of British
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Food and the Empire: The Bikers explore the impact Britain's colonial past has on food, from chai in bread and butter pudding to India pale ale in sausage casserole. S2 Ep13

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Rick Stein's Road to Mexico
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Oaxaca to Chinantlan Mountains: Rick explores the hidden land of Mexico's culinary capital Oaxaca, where you can smell the tropical fruit and Mexico's national cheese of queso oaxacana. S1 Ep6

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Would I Lie To You?
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Surely royalty wouldn't lie? Danny Dyer is among the famous fibbers in the award-winning comedy panel show. Jon Richardson, Joe Lycett and Moira Stuart also adopt poker faces. S9 Ep1

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Richard Osman's House of Games
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Presenter Toby Anstis, comedy actor Kerry Howard, stand-up Evelyn Mok and all-round personality Joe Sugg pit their wits against the best-selling author's tricky challenges. S6 Ep21

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Richard Osman's House of Games
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Gardening expert Diarmuid Gavin, antiques guru Roo Irvine, comedian John Kearns and musician Claire Richards compete to win the Pointless friend's sought-after trophy. S6 Ep26

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: QI XL
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Jungles: The thinking person's comedy quiz show. Trying not to be dense thickets on the subject of jungles are Greg Proops, David O'Doherty, Reginald D Hunter and Alan Davies. S10 Ep10

UAndDavejavu.uk.title: Will & Ralf Should Know Better
UAndDavejavu.uk.description: Teamwork: Will Mellor and Ralf Little test their teamwork skills driving a tank blindfolded, competing in wheelchair basketball, and rescuing 'survivors' during an earthquake emergency. S2 Ep1

DMAXUK.uk.description: The Dirt Dogs' huge dry blower shuts down due to extreme temperatures, while the Mahoneys and Gold Gypsies take a last-minute gamble that delivers big gold. S4, Ep12

DMAXUK.uk.description: Neville and Mick's final hunt of the season is set to deliver another monster nugget. And, Scrappers boss, Alex, pays the ultimate price for gambling his life savings. S4, Ep13

DMAXUK.uk.description: Diamonds in the Rough. The Baggage Battlers are back. Today they visit an auction in Brooklyn, one of the busiest shipping ports in the USA, but will they unearth any treasures? S2, Ep2

DMAXUK.uk.description: Man on Fire. The Baggage Battlers head to Greensboro, which is a major hub for imported and exported goods. But will they unearth any valuable items in the lot at Quality Salvage? S2, Ep1

DMAXUK.uk.title: Chasing Classic Cars
DMAXUK.uk.description: Ford GT40 & A Flying Banana. Wayne takes on a rare '34 MG PA Airline Coupe, helps out on a multi-million-dollar Ford GT40 Mk IV, and finds a unique Aston Martin Speed Model Type C. S10, Ep6

DMAXUK.uk.title: Chasing Classic Cars
DMAXUK.uk.description: Commander In Chief. Wayne's all-original 1954 Studebaker Commander Starliner Coupe is invited to compete in a prestigious car show. And, he gambles on a 1938 Lincoln Model K Coupe. S10, Ep7

DMAXUK.uk.description: Wheels And Deals. Wayne transforms a 1931 Packard 840 Roadster Packard and meets an unexpected buyer. Plus, he loans 'Wheeler Dealers' star Mike Brewer a '57 Ferrari Testa Rossa. S10, Ep8

DMAXUK.uk.description: It Sounds Bitchin', Let's Make It Look Bitchin'. A 69 Camaro has a new owner who wants to finish off the build. Plus, a 1965 Mustang with mechanical issues gets a Bitchin upgrade. S4, Ep4

DMAXUK.uk.description: The One Where Nick Gets Arrested. The guys go to Pleasanton, CA, for a big West Coast car show. But first, they must get a Chevelle road-ready - if the staff aren't arrested. S4, Ep6

DMAXUK.uk.description: VW Camper: A 70s Revival. Ant has found an iconic VW Campervan that's been abandoned mid-restoration. The interior needs a full refit, plus a suspension overhaul. S1, Ep2

DMAXUK.uk.description: The Bermuda Triangle Conspiracy. Jeremy Wade investigates if one of the Bermuda Triangle's most infamous disappearances was part of a conspiracy by a secret agent at war with the US. S1, Ep4

DMAXUK.uk.description: US Navy Vs UFO. Jeremy Wade explores the sinking of the mighty SS Fitzgerald. Can new discoveries finally tell us what led to one of the biggest catastrophes on the Great Lakes? S1, Ep5

DMAXUK.uk.title: Lost Monster Files
DMAXUK.uk.description: Mystery Of The Minnesota Wildman. The team investigates a murder mystery involving the Wildman of Minnesota. They uncover a major find at the farm where the body was last seen. S1, Ep3

DMAXUK.uk.description: Thunderbird Of Pennsylvania. The team investigate sightings of large birds of prey in Chestnut Ridge, PA. They discover what Sanderson believed to be the mysterious thunderbird. S1, Ep4

DMAXUK.uk.description: Ghosts In The Swamp. The team investigate a Texas swamp. The area is filled with snakes but what frightens Phil and Jess are mysterious lights that have haunted locals for decades. S2, Ep3

DMAXUK.uk.title: Expedition X
DMAXUK.uk.description: Terror Of The Bell Witch. The team investigates one of America's oldest witch stories. In the backwoods of Tennessee, locals report being attacked in a vast cave system. S2, Ep4

DMAXUK.uk.description: Devil In The Forest. The team head to the woods of southern New Jersey to hunt for the infamous Jersey Devil, reported to have terrorised locals for more than 300 years. S2, Ep5
